    </article>
    <article class="stage-card" data-accent="green" id="compound">
      <span class="num green">05 Compound</span>
      <h3>Build the appreciating asset →</h3>
      <p>Cloud credits burn. Dashboards rot. But runbooks, verifiers, golden paths, labeled incidents, and deployment muscle can appreciate through use.</p>
      <div class="viz" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 500 240" width="100%" height="100%"><rect width="500" height="240" fill="#06080c"/><path d="M50 55 C120 97 160 132 225 147 C300 165 370 176 455 179" fill="none" stroke="#ff5d5d" stroke-width="3"/><path d="M50 190 C130 182 190 165 245 135 C320 94 375 64 455 52" fill="none" stroke="#18d6a3" stroke-width="3"/><line x1="232" y1="48" x2="232" y2="200" stroke="#8d98aa" stroke-dasharray="5 5"/><text x="55" y="40" fill="#ff5d5d" font-size="11">tribal knowledge, expired dashboards</text><text x="285" y="42" fill="#18d6a3" font-size="11">runbooks, tests, paved roads</text><text x="206" y="220" fill="#586273" font-size="11">operating use</text></svg></div>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="frameworks" id="frameworks">
    <h2 class="section-title">Frameworks</h2>
    <div class="framework-list">
      <a class="framework" href="#map"><b>Service Graph →</b><span>Map services, owners, vendors, queues, and failure paths as one operating graph.</span></a>
      <a class="framework" href="#price"><b>Dollarized SLO →</b><span>Convert uptime, latency, recovery time, and deploy friction into business cost.</span></a>
      <a class="framework" href="#allocate"><b>Platform Portfolio →</b><span>Treat every migration, automation, and hire as an instrument with return and variance.</span></a>
      <a class="framework" href="#ship"><b>Promotion Protocol →</b><span>Move systems from disabled to human-in-the-loop to autonomous through evidence.</span></a>
      <a class="framework" href="#ship"><b>Quality Ratchet →</b><span>Prevent regressions with gates that lock in the floor after every accepted improvement.</span></a>
      <a class="framework" href="#compound"><b>Runbook Capital →</b><span>Turn incidents into verifiers, documentation, drills, and paved paths that appreciate.</span></a>
      <a class="framework" href="#allocate"><b>Org Constraint Map →</b><span>Price attention, review queues, team topology, and political debt as hard constraints.</span></a>
      <a class="framework" href="#price"><b>Kill Criteria →</b><span>Define when to stop a project before sunk cost, sponsorship, and momentum distort the portfolio.</span></a>
